        <num>CCP 3507.1</num>
        <heading>3507.1.  Release of property by plaintiff; security</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3507.1.  Release of property by plaintiff; security
Property seized under a writ of attachment or of sequestration may be released to the plaintiff upon proof of his ownership and upon furnishing security as required by Article 3508.  All costs incurred as a result of the seizure shall be paid by the plaintiff prior to the release of the property.  A written agreement to hold the seizing authority harmless for wrongful seizure of property which is not seized to enforce a security interest, mortgage, lien or privilege may be substituted in lieu of security at the discretion of the sheriff.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111783</p>
        </authorialNote>
